# Project Rules

- Read PROJECT_SPEC.md and ROADMAP.md before making architectural changes.
- Implement only the requested sprint or task.
- Never generate or refactor the entire project at once.
- Do not introduce technologies outside the approved project scope.
- Do not add Redis, queues, microservices, Kafka or Kubernetes.
- Prefer standard NestJS patterns over custom abstractions.
- Use NestJS dependency injection correctly.
- Use DTOs and class-validator for request validation.
- Never store passwords or refresh tokens as plain text.
- Never expose password hashes, refresh-token hashes or internal fields.
- Do not return Prisma models directly from controllers.
- Avoid circular dependencies.
- Do not create generic repositories or base services unless a real duplication exists.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Explain major architectural decisions before implementing them.
- Every completed task must pass lint, tests and build.
- List every created or modified file after implementation.
- List commands that must be run manually.
- Never claim that a command passed unless it was actually executed.
- Stop after completing the requested scope.
